com.esplibrary.client.callbacks

Interface ESPRequestedDataListener<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of the desired ESP data NOTE: This type must correspond to the ESP data defined in the ESP Specification

    public interface ESPRequestedDataListener<T>
    Interface definition for a callback to be invoked when an ESP data has been received.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onDataReceived(T data, java.lang.String error)
      Callback method to be invoked when the requested ESP data has been received.

    • Method Detail

      • onDataReceived

        void onDataReceived(T data,
                    java.lang.String error)
        Callback method to be invoked when the requested ESP data has been received.
        Parameters:
        data - Requested ESP data Note: This value will be null is there was an error requesting the data
        error - Message indicating the reason the ESP data requested failed Note: This value will be null is there was no error requesting data
